                  <msItem>
                     <p>
                        <placeName key="place_111667">Needham-Street etc</placeName>. 
                        <origDate when="1315">1315</origDate>. 
                        Grant from <persName><forename>Robert</forename> le <surname>Fole</surname> of <placeName role="person">Kenteford</placeName>, miller</persName>, to <persName><forename>Walter</forename> <surname>Priour</surname> of <placeName role="person">Nedham, in the parish of Gayslee</placeName></persName>, and <persName nymRef="Priour"><forename>Petronilla</forename> his wife</persName>, for certain sum of money, of two acres of arable land, in four parcels, lying at the upper end of the parish of <placeName>Gayslee</placeName>, in the field called <placeName type="minor">Caremenecroftes</placeName>, next to the land of <persName><forename>Thomas</forename> <surname>Beyllard</surname></persName>, one end abutting on the common heath, the other on the land of <persName><forename>Gilbert</forename> <surname>Mariscal</surname></persName>.
                     Dated at <placeName role="date">Nedham</placeName>, Monday [1 Dec.] before the feast of St Nicholas, bishop and confessor, 9 Edw. II [1315].
                     Witnesses: <persName><forename>Walter</forename> <surname>Mercer</surname></persName>, <persName><forename>William</forename> <surname>Sperlyng</surname></persName>, <persName><forename>Gilbert</forename> <surname>Mariscal</surname></persName>, <persName><forename>Richard</forename> le <surname>Warner</surname></persName>, <persName><forename>Ralph</forename> <surname>(Townsend) 'ad caput ville'</surname></persName>, <persName><forename>John</forename> <surname>Dersoun</surname></persName>, <persName><forename>Robert</forename> <surname>(Smith) 'Fabro'</surname> of <placeName role="person">Nedham</placeName></persName>, and others.
                     The seal is wanting.
                     [Chandler deeds]
                     </p>
                  </msItem>
